                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190707-97-victim888 t18190707-97-viclabel526"></join>, and live in Euston-crescent. On the 15th of June, in the morning, I missed the wheels, and axletree of my truck out of the area. I saw them again about a week after in the prisoner's possession. He said he gave a cart in exchange for them.</p>
               <p>NEWEY TRALLAGAN. I work for Richards. I put the axletree and wheels in the area, and afterwards missed them. I found the wheels in a wheeler's yard afterward.</p>
               <p>(Axletree produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I bartered a small cart for them.</p>
